headline: The maker of Taser is the highest paid CEO, taking home $165 million—his new pay package and soaring stock made him a billionaire last year
summary: Smith says he founded the $17 billion company after two of his friends were shot—but the tragic backstory, which has been core to the company’s ethos, may be a myth.
